cs.HC, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.MM

The paper focuses on designing a photo description feature for the Facebook mobile application to improve the photo-sharing experiences of visually impaired people. This involves incorporating computer-generated descriptions using computer vision techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), followed by Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as they are directly related to the design and implementation of the photo description feature. Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Multimedia (cs.MM) are also likely categories as the paper discusses the use of social networking services and visual content sharing.
